The paper deals with facial landmarks detection, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes a new framework for regression-based facial landmarks detection, which involves training a single self-iterative regressor, and hence it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning-based methods, which makes it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of regression-based methods, which can be considered as a subfield of neural networks, and hence it is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category as well.
